<li><a href="#Subscription-services-solidify-customer-loyalty">Subscription services solidify customer loyalty</a></li>
<li><a href="#AI-fuels-customized-buying-journeys">AI fuels customized buying journeys</a></li>
<li><a href="#Dynamic,-personalized-websites-go-mainstream">Dynamic, personalized websites go mainstream</a></li>
<li><a href="#Ecommerce-brands-will-launch-more-data-gathering-campaigns">Ecommerce brands will launch more data-gathering campaigns</a></li>
</ol>
<h2>9 ecommerce trends to monitor in 2024</h2>
<p>The <a href="https://www.couponcabin.com/blog/online-shopping-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ecommerce shopping statistics</a> tell us things are changing. And what do those numbers say? These are the most high-profile ecommerce marketing trends we see heading our way this year. Learn them to stay in tune with customers and ahead of competitors.</p>
<div id="Conversational-marketing-becomes-table-stakes-for-ecommerce-brands"></div>
<h3>1. Conversational marketing becomes table stakes for ecommerce brands</h3>
<p>Conversational marketing is a strategy where businesses have two-way communication with customers in real time. Those one-to-one interactions can happen with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/05/08/live-chat-rulebook">live agents</a>, but a lot of conversational marketing growth will occur with AI-powered <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/chatbots">chatbots</a>.</p>
<p>For example, one study suggests that by 2028, around <a href="https://www.juniperresearch.com/press/retail-spend-over-chatbots-to-reach-12bn-globally/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">$72 billion</a> in retail spending will happen through chatbot interactions. For context, that‚Äôs a 470% increase compared to the $12 billion in chatbot sales from 2023.</p>
<p>Two factors are fueling this ecommerce trend: generative AI and consumers‚Äô desire for fast answers.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/05/generative-ai-in-digital-marketing">Generative AI</a> models like ChatGPT use natural language processing to understand conversational queries. That‚Äôs helped chatbots become highly successful sales agents that can guide website visitors through their buying journey.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-conversational-marketing-1.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - chatbot from Seattle Balloon company. " width="434" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82400 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-conversational-marketing-1.webp 434w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-conversational-marketing-1-217x300.webp 217w" sizes="(max-width: 434px) 100vw, 434px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://seattleballooning.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>For most consumers, the <a href="https://thechatbot.net/statistics-chatbot-ai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">most significant upside</a> of using chatbots is the 24/7 availability of information. Instead of waiting until regular business hours, shoppers can jump in when inspiration strikes and get all the information they need to make an informed purchase.</p>
<p>The great news is chatbots are becoming less expensive and easier to launch, so expect to see them gain traction in <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/ai-in-marketing-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">smaller businesses</a>. You can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/02/04/how-to-build-a-chatbot-your-brand">launch your own chatbot</a> in a jiffy.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Conversational marketing relies on great calls to action. Download this free guide to get inspired by dozens of <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite36CallToActionPhrases.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_36CallToActionPhrases_Download">high-performing CTA phrases</a>.</p>
<div id="Ecommerce-businesses-will-find-new-uses-for-AR"></div>
<h3>2. Ecommerce businesses will find new uses for AR</h3>
<p>The virtual reality (VR) craze hit its peak when <a href="https://about.fb.com/news/2021/10/facebook-company-is-now-meta/#:~:text=Introducing%20Meta%3A%20A%20Social%20Technology%20Company&amp;text=Today%20at%20Connect%202021%2C%20CEO,find%20communities%20and%20grow%20businesses." target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook rebranded as Meta</a>, a signal that the social media giant was turning its vast resources towards developing online worlds known loosely as the metaverse. Despite some optimistic forecasts, most of us still aren‚Äôt guiding our avatars down digital promenades in search of the next digital deal. And with Meta still <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/02/01/metas-reality-labs-loses-4point65-billion-in-q4-ahead-of-vision-pro.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">losing millions</a> on its big VR bet, it‚Äôs unlikely to happen any time soon.</p>
<p>However, an interesting movement in ecommerce is taking advantage of augmented reality, VR‚Äôs cousin that overlays digital imagery on real-world environments in real time.</p>
<p>AR has become very accessible, even offered as free features like stickers and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-do-a-poll-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">polls</a> on social media platforms. Expect to see online retailers and brands taking advantage of AR in new ways. For example, fashion brands use AR to help mobile shoppers see how they‚Äôll look in this season‚Äôs styles.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-VR-1.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - screenshot of a VR eyeglass try on screen." width="936" height="483" class="aligncenter wp-image-82401 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-VR-1.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-VR-1-480x248.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.smartbuyglasses.co.uk/virtual-try-on" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Users snap a picture in the brand‚Äôs app, and AR adds the products. Clothing brands, household goods, and even car dealers are all using AR to help buyers make a purchase decision.</p>
<p>Other retailers are using AR to highlight product details, like price tags or features, in promotional videos.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-AR-price.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - shopping video with AR price tags." width="328" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82399 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-AR-price.webp 328w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-AR-price-164x300.webp 164w" sizes="(max-width: 328px) 100vw, 328px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/vxcam-ar-video-text-labels/id1352777505" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>With AR&#8217;s near-zero cost for these use cases and more app developers building creative AR solutions, expect to see it used more often and by a wider variety of ecommerce businesses.</p>
<div id="More-sellers-slide-into-their-customers-DMs"></div>
<h3>3. More sellers slide into their customers‚Äô DMs</h3>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-dm-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Direct messaging</a>, like the DMs on your Instagram or TikTok account, is ideal for brands to interact with customers and fans one-on-one. You can send links, images, and product videos. Plus, it doesn‚Äôt cost anything to send a DM. That‚Äôs why we‚Äôll see more brands connect with their customers in direct message apps this year.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-DMs-two.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - Promotional direct message." width="348" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82389 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-DMs-two.webp 348w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-DMs-two-174x300.webp 174w" sizes="(max-width: 348px) 100vw, 348px" /></p>
<p>Because of their private nature, DMs are a great place to have <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-respond-to-negative-reviews/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">conversations about customer concerns</a>. You can even use them as a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/lead-generation-ideas">lead generation channel</a> as an alternative to collecting email addresses on your website.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-DMs.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - Lead generation campaign on Instagram." width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82388 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-DMs.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-DMs-480x308.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CR87iQzFCpq/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>A word of warning if you want to try this trend out for yourself. If you start messaging random people, you‚Äôll definitely get blocked and probably reported. Always ask before contacting someone in their DMs. Offer a reason, like giving someone a personal discount code or asking them to share their experience with your products (free <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/04/28/user-generated-content">user-generated content</a>!).</p>
<div id="Gen-Z-spurs-shift-to-social-shopping"></div>
<h3>4. Gen Z spurs shift to social shopping</h3>
<p>At first, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/social-media-marketing">social media marketing</a> was mainly a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/07/10/brand-awareness">brand awareness</a> play. Sellers could share their wares in organic and paid posts and then offer links to their e-commerce shops.</p>
<p>Jumping from one platform to the next adds friction to the sales process. With <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/04/25/social-shopping">social shopping</a>, consumers can click on the products they see in a post and complete the purchase without leaving their favorite social media apps.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-social-selling.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - Shoppable facebook post from Nike." width="828" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82395 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-social-selling.webp 828w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-social-selling-480x348.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 828px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Revenue from social commerce could hit the <a href="https://www.statista.com/topics/8757/social-commerce/#topicOverview" target="_blank" rel="noopener">trillion</a> (with a ‚ÄúT‚Äù) dollar mark in the next few years. Younger adults lead the charge, with nearly <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1455174/worldwide-share-of-shoppers-purchasing-via-social-media-by-age/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">three-quarters</a> of 18 to 34-year-olds saying they‚Äôve made a purchase from social commerce. But the trend is also permeating through all generations‚Äîaround 25% of consumers over 65 said they‚Äôve bought through that channel as well. With that kind of cross-generational spread, we expect to see a lot a lot more sales through social selling activities.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Download the newly updated <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteAllStarPlaybook.html?cid=Web_Blog_InContent_TextLink_AllStarPlaybook_Download">All-Star Advertising Playbook</a> to get expert-level tips for all four of the most lucrative advertising channels.</p>
<div id="Live-commerce-bridges-the-gap-between-online-and-in-person-shopping"></div>
<h3>5. Live commerce bridges the gap between online and in-person shopping</h3>
<p>If QVC and social shopping had a love child, it would be live commerce. During a live commerce event, a host interacts with viewers via video on a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/11/most-popular-social-media-platforms">social media platform</a>. Those viewers can then purchase the products on offer right from the video.</p>
<p>Live commerce offers the best parts of in-store shopping without fighting traffic or searching for a parking space. Shoppers get instant answers from a knowledgeable brand representative or influencer right from their living room.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-live-shopping-one.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - live shopping example." width="462" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82393 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-live-shopping-one.webp 462w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-live-shopping-one-231x300.webp 231w" sizes="(max-width: 462px) 100vw, 462px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://business.instagram.com/blog/instagram-live-shopping-reach-customers" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>The most popular social media apps are participating in this trend. Instagram and TikTok offer live shopping features, and <a href="https://blog.youtube/news-and-events/youtube-shopify-integration-merch-shopping/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a> inked a deal with Shopify to let creators add shoppable links to videos.</p>
<p>While the most common format for live shopping involves one or two representatives on screen touting the brand‚Äôs latest and greatest, there‚Äôs another interesting way to use this tactic. Say you‚Äôre launching a new line of cosmetics. You could have a launch party and let viewers buy what they see on their screens.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-live-shopping-two.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - Live shopping example on YouTube." width="357" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82394 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-live-shopping-two.webp 357w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-live-shopping-two-179x300.webp 179w" sizes="(max-width: 357px) 100vw, 357px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://blog.youtube/news-and-events/youtube-shopify-integration-merch-shopping/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>The live commerce trend is expected to grow significantly in the near term, with some suggesting it could account for <a href="https://www.businessdit.com/live-commerce-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">20%</a> of all ecommerce sales. Since conversion rates at live shopping events can reach 30%, ecommerce brands would be wise to take advantage of this trend.</p>
<div id="Subscription-services-solidify-customer-loyalty"></div>
<h3>6. Subscription services solidify customer loyalty</h3>
<p>Buy almost any consumable from Amazon, and you‚Äôll be asked if you‚Äôd like to save a few dollars by subscribing to auto-refill your order. The initial loss in profit to the seller is well worth the higher potential of repeat business. And the buyer sees the savings as a no-brainer since they‚Äôll need more of the product later.</p>
<p>The trend goes beyond monthly dog food or cosmetics deliveries (although those are common). Now, you can get a regular delivery of all sorts of themed products, like miniature items for your doll house or train set.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-subscription.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - Promotional social post for a subscription deal." width="374" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82396 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-subscription.webp 374w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-subscription-187x300.webp 187w" sizes="(max-width: 374px) 100vw, 374px" /></p>
<p>Savings and customer loyalty are powerful win-wins that are likely to motivate sellers and shoppers to keep the trend going. <a href="https://www.ebbo.com/insights/blog/subscription-loyalty-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">77%</a> of consumers say they spend up to $499 annually on subscriptions, and 41% say they‚Äôll add more in the next year.</p>
<div id="AI-fuels-customized-buying-journeys"></div>
<h3>7. AI fuels customized buying journeys</h3>
<p>In general, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-marketing-trends-2024">AI is a big trend</a> for all marketers. There are many ways ecommerce brands and marketers can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/05/generative-ai-in-digital-marketing">use artificial intelligence</a> to boost their businesses. One that‚Äôs emerging as particularly useful is having AI create complex, personalized customer journeys.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs an example. Say you send marketing texts to your customers, reminding them of sales and new products. If each text of those campaigns were personalized to the individual based on their prior behavior, you‚Äôd close a lot more sales. But it‚Äôd be nearly impossible to do manually when you‚Äôre promoting hundreds of products to thousands of customers.</p>
<p>That‚Äôs where <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-in-marketing">marketing experts are applying AI</a>. Using its machine learning capabilities, AI can ‚Äúremember‚Äù how customers reacted to previous messages, which products they bought, and how they interacted with your website. Then, it can create a custom campaign for each text subscriber.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-AI-journey.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - Example of a promotional SMS text flow.," width="698" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82398 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-AI-journey.webp 698w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-AI-journey-480x413.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 698px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.attentive.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Personalization is a well-documented marketing strategy that often lifts revenue by up to <a href="https://www.mckinsey.com/capabilities/growth-marketing-and-sales/our-insights/the-value-of-getting-personalization-right-or-wrong-is-multiplying" target="_blank" rel="noopener">25%</a>. Brands that use advanced personalization strategies say they see a <a href="https://www.businessdit.com/personalization-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">200%</a> return on the investment.</p>
<p>In the coming year, we‚Äôll see many more retailers and brands use AI to construct personalized buying journeys through <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/21/promotional-email-examples">promotional emails</a>, texts, and social media, individually and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/22/cross-channel-marketing">across multiple channels</a>.</p>
<div id="Dynamic,-personalized-websites-go-mainstream"></div>
<h3>8. Dynamic, personalized websites go mainstream</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/personalized-marketing">Personalization</a> has been the playground of ad campaigns for a while. But what if every person who visited your promotional <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/great-landing-pages">landing page</a> or home page saw a version that best suited their needs? That‚Äôs what <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/dynamic-landing-pages">dynamic landing pages</a> and websites offer.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs a simple example where someone considering your product sees a different home page than someone who bought it.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-dynamic-website.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - two landing pages with different text for customers and prospects." width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82390 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-dynamic-website.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-dynamic-website-480x308.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Dynamic landing pages aren‚Äôt new. What‚Äôs changed is the scale and scope of personalization available with new AI-powered techniques, making them more attractive to ecommerce shops with many product and sales pages.</p>
<p>Let‚Äôs say you have a website with hundreds of sales and conversion pages. AI can analyze huge amounts of data about your products and customer behavior. Then, generative AI can quickly create <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/05/conversational-tone">conversational copy</a> or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/10/09/call-to-action">calls to action</a> for each of those pages that are more relevant to each segment of your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/09/18/beginners-guide-to-target-markets">target market</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://fibr.ai/blog/significance-of-dynamic-landing-pages-for-your-website" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Most marketers</a> that use personalized landing pages report a lift in engagement compared to static versions. Plus, 91% of customers said they felt more connected with websites featuring dynamic pages, especially those that provided personalized offers and product recommendations.</p>
<div id="Ecommerce-brands-will-launch-more-data-gathering-campaigns"></div>
<h3>9. Ecommerce brands will launch more data-gathering campaigns</h3>
<p>Many of the trends we‚Äôve discussed require extensive data about your customers. Gathering this information has pros and cons. Some shoppers love the personalization it provides, while others are rightfully concerned about their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/22/customer-data-privacy">privacy</a>.</p>
<p>In light of these concerns, lawmakers and big platforms are making it harder to collect data without direct user consent. Google has finally <a href="https://www.emarketer.com/content/google-turns-off-cookies-30-million-chrome-users-that-s-just-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ended the use of third-party cookies</a>. Some US states and European governments require websites to give visitors a choice to opt in or opt out of being tracked by cookies.</p>
<p>With much less third-party data, ecommerce marketers will need to become really good at convincing shoppers to give up their information willingly, also known as zero-party data.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-data-types.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - Graphic showing types of data." width="936" height="572" class="aligncenter wp-image-82387 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-data-types.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-data-types-480x293.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>In the coming months and years, we&#8217;ll see more creative campaigns designed to<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/customer-data"> collect data</a> from willing website visitors and customers ethically. These may be contests, newsletter subscriptions, surveys, or even discounts and free products.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-gather-data.webp" alt="Ecommerce trends - giveaway to collect email addresses." width="931" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82392 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-gather-data.webp 931w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ecommerce-trends-wordstream-gather-data-480x309.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 931px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>However it‚Äôs done, collecting zero-party data is a big ecommerce marketing trend that almost every retailer and brand needs to be aware of.</p>
<h2>What is the future of the ecommerce industry?</h2>
<p>To say last year was one of change for ecommerce stores and marketers is a drastic understatement. With the rapid development of new <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-copywriting-tools">AI marketing tools</a>, customers‚Äô shift to new sales channels, and potential regulations that can change how everyone does business online, it‚Äôs nearly impossible to guess the future of ecommerce with 100% clarity.</p>
<p>But if you look at the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2025-marketing-tips">marketing trends</a> ramping up now, you‚Äôll see a few themes that hint at the future. Customers want in-store experiences from online shopping. They‚Äôll choose lower-friction purchase options over clicking through multiple apps and websites. And they‚Äôd prefer personalized interactions as long as their privacy remains protected.</p>
<p>While you mull over what‚Äôs to come for ecommerce stores, have a look at these other marketing trends for further insights:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ppc-for-retail">PPC for Retail: Biggest Trends, Challenges, &amp; Strategies for Success</a></li>
